Request Transfer Out

This page is for current ARAD licensees requesting to transfer out. You can transfer to another brokerage or back to the State of Nevada (inactive).

{/* CLEANER INFO TYPOGRAPHY */}

ARAD processes transfer requests by preparing and mailing the required paperwork to the Nevada Real Estate Division. A copy is emailed to you for your records.

NOTE: ARAD only mails transfer paperwork to the Division via US Mail. We do not complete transfer paperwork in person and we do not release licenses to be hand carried.

What happens after you submit:

  1. We prepare the state paperwork and mail it with your original license.
  2. The Division posts your license as Inactive (typically 3–5 business days).
  3. You can track status here:  Nevada License Lookup .
  4. You then complete the state association form to join your new brokerage.
